From  <a href="http://faculty.marianopolis.edu/c.belanger/QuebecHistory/encyclopedia/EdsonJosephChamberlin-QuebecHistory.htm">faculty.marianopolis.edu/c.belanger/QuebecHistory/encyclo...</a> 
&quot;Chamberlin, Edson Joseph  (1852-1924), president of the Grand Trunk Railway (1912-17), was born in Lancaster, New Hampshire, on August 25, 1852 . He was educated at the Montpelier Methodist Seminary, and in 1871 entered the service of a New England railway. In 1886 he became general manager of the Canada Atlantic Railway, and in 1909 general manager and vice-president of the Grand Trunk Railway. In 1912 he became president of this railway, but he resigned in 1917. He died at Pasadena, California, on August 27, 1924. &quot;

Another Canadian biographical site shows the same photograph, at <a href="http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/chamberlin_ej.shtml">www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/chamberlin_ej.shtml</a>
